      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "lightly oil a non-stick baking sheet",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "To make the cinder toffee, heat the sugar and syrup gently in a big deep pan. Wait for the sugar to melt into a clear syrup. Then boil the mix until it turns a deep golden caramel.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Whisk in the bicarbonate of soda (this will make it foam up) then quickly pour it onto the oiled baking sheet and cool. Break into bite-sized pieces.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Put the condensed milk, cream and vanilla into a large bowl. Beat with an electric whisk until softly whipped.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Fold in the pieces of cinder toffee.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Tip into a freezer container, cover and freeze.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Use a sugar thermometer. Stages: soft-ball 115°C, hard-ball 125°C, soft-crack 135°C, hard-crack 150°C. Cold-water tests work but the thermometer doesn't lie.",
              "cause": "Sugar didn't reach the right stage, or temperature was guessed.",
              "symptom": "Mixture won't set"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Don't stir once the sugar is dissolved. Brush the inside of the pan with a wet pastry brush to wash crystals down.",
              "cause": "Mixture stirred after it started bubbling, or a stray crystal landed on the side of the pan.",
              "symptom": "Sugar crystallised"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Cool to 43°C before beating. The mixture turns from glossy to matte when ready to set.",
              "cause": "Beaten too soon. While still too hot.",
              "symptom": "Fudge is grainy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Add a teaspoon of warm cream or water and stir until smooth, this is the trick. Drier seizing needs more liquid; thin seizing wants less.",
              "cause": "Water touched melted chocolate.",
              "symptom": "Mixture seized into a ball"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Flavoured version: stir in a teaspoon of vanilla, almond, or peppermint extract once the mixture is off the heat.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Dip-coated: once set, dip pieces in melted dark chocolate and let drip on baking paper.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Made days in advance and lives in the freezer.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
